We shall further note the BdG equation has particle-hole symmetry, where
 equations are invariant under interchange of 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray}
E_{{\bf k}} & \leftrightarrow & -E_{-{\bf k}}\nonumber \\
\left(\begin{array}{c}
u_{{\bf k}}\\
\alpha_{{\bf k}}\\
\beta_{{\bf k}}\\
v_{{\bf k}}\end{array}\right) & \leftrightarrow & \left(\begin{array}{c}
\beta_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}\\
v_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}\\
u_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}\\
\alpha_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}\end{array}\right)\label{eq:particleholesymmetry}\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

For instance, we start from 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
m_{11}({\bf k}+\frac{q}{2}{\bf e}_{z})u_{{\bf k}}+(v_{1}k_{x}-iv_{2}k_{y})\alpha_{{\bf k}}-\Delta({\bf x})e^{-iqz}v_{{\bf k}}=E_{{\bf k}}u_{{\bf k}}\end{equation}

\end_inset

and we make the particle-hole interchange,
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
m_{11}({\bf k}+\frac{q}{2}{\bf e}_{z})\beta_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}+(v_{1}k_{x}-iv_{2}k_{y})v_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}-\Delta({\bf x})e^{-iqz}\alpha_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}=-E_{-{\bf k}}\beta_{-{\bf k}}^{\ast}\end{equation}

\end_inset

