where we have abbreviated 
\begin_inset Formula $[u_{n},\alpha_{n},\beta_{n},v_{n}]$
\end_inset

 into 
\begin_inset Formula $[u,\alpha,\beta,v]$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $a=\kappa_{1}^{(0)}\approx2.40483$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $b=\kappa_{1}^{(1)}\approx3.83171$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray}
\mathcal{N}_{1}^{(0)} & = & \int_{0}^{1}J_{0}(\kappa_{1}^{(0)}r)J_{0}(\kappa_{1}^{(0)}r)rdr=\frac{1}{2}\left(J_{1}(\kappa_{1}^{(0)})\right)^{2}\equiv A^{2}\approx0.134757\\
\mathcal{N}_{1}^{(1)} & = & \int_{0}^{1}J_{1}(\kappa_{1}^{(1)}r)J_{1}(\kappa_{1}^{(1)}r)rdr=\frac{1}{2}\left(J_{2}(\kappa_{1}^{(1)})\right)^{2}\equiv B^{2}\approx0.081107\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

Then we recast the eigen equation of BdG Hamiltonian into coefficient matrix,
